snippet.textDisplay:
I am sad that the weaver ants had to go. The video where you released them into their setup is what really gave me an appreciation for ants. Until then I saw ants as a nuisance and perhaps even to the point that I hated them. When I saw the ants explore and get excited about their new enclosure it made me see them in a new light.


I hope in the future the species can return, but for now I hope they are doing well out in the wild.

snippet.textDisplay: Stay safe during these tough times.  I have been out of work for almost a month at this point due to social distancing.  Your channel has been a definite help getting through the isolation, as well as inspiration.  Myrmecocystus Mexicanus and Navajo are native species to my home state, and thanks to your forum pages I know their nuptial flights are in July.  I've started collect supplies to build them a stellar home, and give ants a try.  I have had success with reptiles, amphibians and invertebrates for a long time, this will be my first attempt at an ant colony.  Thank you for the beautiful work you create, and I hope to share my babies with you soon.
snippet.textOriginal: Stay safe during these tough times.  I have been out of work for almost a month at this point due to social distancing.  Your channel has been a definite help getting through the isolation, as well as inspiration.
